### 1. Removed `FIRST_ROWS(30)` — Replaced with Targeted Hints
The original hint `/*+ FIRST_ROWS(30) */` is a throughput-vs-response-time hint that biased the optimizer toward Nested Loops but was placed only on the innermost subquery and ignored at the join level. The explain plan proves it failed — both BSIS and BKPF were fully scanned. It was replaced with three precise, scope-correct hints on the outer query:

